Package org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.tree.as Description

This package is the internal counterpart of the external org.apache.flex.compiler.tree.as package.

It contains classes that implement the AS node interfaces. After the AST for a compilation unit has been built, you should access nodes only through the external interfaces and never through these internal classes. The methods in the interfaces are guaranteed to be safe to call from multiple threads, while the methods in these classes are not.

See the description of the org.apache.flex.compiler package for an explanation of how the compiler code is organized into external and internal packages.
